@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    JKL Healthcare is committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. 
    This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose your information in compliance with 
    relevant data protection laws, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the Data 
    Protection Act 2018.
</p>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>
<p>
    We collect the following types of information:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Patient information: Name, address, medical records (encrypted), and other relevant details.</li>
    <li>Caregiver information: Name, contact details, qualifications, and availability.</li>
    <li>User information: Username, password (hashed), and role (administrator or caregiver).</li>
</ul>

<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>
    We use your information to:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Provide and improve healthcare services.</li>
    <li>Manage patient care and caregiver assignments.</li>
    <li>Schedule appointments.</li>
    <li>Communicate with patients and caregivers.</li>
    <li>Generate reports and analyze data to improve our services.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Data Security</h2>
<p>
    We take appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your information from unauthorized 
    access, use, or disclosure. These measures include:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Encryption of sensitive data (e.g., medical records).</li>
    <li>Access controls to limit access to information based on user roles.</li>
    <li>Secure storage of data.</li>
    <li>Regular security assessments and updates.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Your Rights</h2>
<p>
    You have the following rights regarding your personal information:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Right to access: You can request access to your information.</li>
    <li>Right to rectification: You can request correction of inaccurate information.</li>
    <li>Right to erasure: You can request deletion of your information in certain circumstances.</li>
    <li>Right to restriction of processing: You can request restriction of processing in certain circumstances.</li>
    <li>Right to data portability: You can request a copy of your information in a portable format.</li>
</ul>

<p>
    If you have any questions or concerns about our privacy policy or your data protection rights, 
    please contact us at [your contact information].
</p>